Woking Greens Network

Summary

The air quality monitors seems to be operating properly. There is a good concordance between each station. Station #7 shows a worse data coverage. It needs further investigation. The basic statistics, analysis in time and backwards trajectories are below.

Woking seems to do not have intense pollution sources, besides the vehicular fleet. The diurnal variation presents higher levels of PM in the night (7 pm to 7 am) and in the weekends.

The episodes of intense pollution are associated with air parcels coming from east, passing through London. The days without polluted episodes have parcels coming from west.

Data consistency
